{
  "texts": [
    "However, XAI may expose critical aspects of the LLMs, including their architecture, components, and the dynamic weight allocation by attention mechanism that contribute to predictions.",
    "Such disclosures may increase the LLM's vulnerability to security and privacy attacks.",
    "For example, revealing the white-box nature of the model may facilitate the attacker's access to the model, increasing the risk of gradient leakage attacks or MIA [63].",
    "Recent studies have claimed that explainability in LLMs may raise further security concerns, especially with insidious backdoor attacks [35].",
    "proposed an XAI approach that can identify the triggers (backdoor attack) that mislead the model to contribute to error classification [141]."
  ]
}